Tunde Oyekola, Ilorin The governor of Kwara State, AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq and the Speaker of the House of Assembly, on Wednesday, congratulated the two state’s nominees into the Federal Character Commission. Two of the state’s indigenes: Hajia Fareedah Dankaka and Mr. James Kolo, were nominated to serve as chairperson and member of the commission respectively. The two were nominated along with 35 others as members of the FCC by the President, Major General Mohammadu Buhari (retd.), and read at the plenary by the Senate President, Ahmed Lawan. In a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Rafiu Ajakaye the governor said, “Our heartfelt congratulations and best wishes go to the two nominees. The nomination is a reward for loyalty to a good cause, a conviction to stick to the truth, and long-standing commitments to the service of humanity especially the good people of Kwara State. “We commend Mr President for this honour. The government and people of Kwara State are very grateful for the recognition to have our daughter and son serve in the A-list parastatal. We are confident that Hajia Fareedah and Mr Kolo will make us proud in the course of this call to serve our fatherland.” Also, the Speaker of the state House of Assembly, Yakubu Danladi in a statement signed by his Special Assistant, Media, Ibrahim Sheriff, described the two nominees “as committed persons to the ideals of the All Progressives Congress and a better Kwara we can all be proud of.” Copyright PUNCH.
